## 🔍 What I Learned

Today I focused on SQL Injection and completed an authentication lab from PortSwigger.

### SQL Injection:
- SQL Injection occurs when user input is not properly sanitized
- Attackers can manipulate queries to bypass authentication or extract data
- Common entry points: login forms, search bars, URL parameters

### Authentication Lab:
- Tested login functionality for vulnerabilities
- Observed how improper validation can allow unauthorized access
- Learned how small input changes affect server responses

## 🧪 What I Practiced
- Identifying injection points
- Modifying input fields to test behavior
- Understanding how backend queries might be structured

## 💡 Key Takeaway
Security is not just about building systems, but also about handling user input correctly. Even basic flaws can lead to serious vulnerabilities.

